Salesforce CLI Enhancements

Use Salesforce CLI to create environments for development and testing, synchronize source code, run tests, and control your application lifecycle.

We release new versions of Salesforce CLI weekly. Here’s a taste of some of the new and changed features we recently delivered; these changes apply to Salesforce CLI version 2.44.8 and later.

Source Mobility (Beta)
Move source files inside your local Salesforce DX project without source-tracking thinking that you’ve deleted and then recreated a metadata component. To use this opt-in beta feature, set the SF_BETA_TRACK_FILE_MOVES environment variable to true. Then reorganize your files as you like!

Improved data Commands (Beta)
Import and export test data more easily with the improved data import|export tree commands.

Decompose More Metadata Types (Beta)
Track changes in custom labels, permission sets, sharing rules, and workflows more easily by specifying that Salesforce CLI decompose their large metadata files into smaller and easily digestible source files.

Refresh a Sandbox from Salesforce CLI
Easily refresh a sandbox from the command line with the new org refresh sandbox CLI command.

Store Flag Values in Local Text Files
Simplify and shorten long CLI commands by storing flag values in local text files. 

More Colorful Help
The --help output of all commands now uses colors to highlight the different parts. If you don’t like the default colors, you can customize them.
title: Salesforce CLI Enhancements for Summer '24
